      <note class="your-turn" id="note-00006">
      <exercise id="exer-00006">
      <problem id="prob-00006">
      <para id="para-00033"><link class="os-embed" url="#exercise/CM-C08-M3-003"/></para>
      </problem>
      </exercise>
      </note>
      <para id="para-00035">Now, let’s tackle an example with an even number of values.</para>
      <example id="exam-00004">
      <title>Finding the Median</title>
      <exercise id="exer-00007">
      <problem id="prob-00007">
      <para id="para-00036">Earlier, we looked at the number of times different crickets (of differing species, genders, etc.) chirped in a one-minute span. Here are the raw data:
      <table summary="." class="unnumbered" id="table-00009">
      <tgroup cols="6">
      <colspec colnum="1" colname="c1" colwidth="1*"/>
      <colspec colnum="2" colname="c2" colwidth="1*"/>
